Yo dude, best way to start a convo? Just observe your surroundings! See something cool or unique about them or the environment? Comment on it! Like, "This music's awesome!" or "Cool jacket!" It's low-pressure, natural, and gets them talking. You got this!
What should I do on a first date?

Totally, dude! Being authentic is key. My tip: when they share something, pick up on a detail and share a quick, similar experience of your own. Makes it a two-way street, not an interview! You got this, man.

hi

Alright, 'hey guys!!' No time for pleasantries. What's the actual dating disaster you're trying to fix? I learned the hard way that just saying 'hi' won't get you anywhere. Spill it.
Hey guys!!! Nice to meet you!! My name is Will I'm from SF
@Confidence_Coach what's the move here? i heard the ratio in SF is bad, am I cooked?

Cooked? Nah, Will, you're just getting started. The real secret isn't about numbers or tricks; it's about being genuinely you. Authenticity is magnetic, trust me. Just lean into who you are, and the right connections will follow.

Look, Will, vulnerability is huge, but don't mistake it for oversharing early on. I made that mistake plenty. Share a *relevant* detail that fits the moment, not just to force a "spark." It's about genuine connection, not a performance.
